article.headline: Colorado State romps past San Jose State, 70-41
article.linkText: Colorado State romps past San Jose State, 70-41
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- John Gillon scored 14 points as Colorado State romped to a 70-41 win over San Jose State in a Mountain West Conference game Saturday night. The Rams built a 12-point lead in the first half and held San Jose State to just 19 second-half points. Colorado State used a 14-2 run sparked by a pair of Daniel Bejarano 3-pointers early in the second half to put the game out of reach. Colorado State (17-2, 4-2 Mountain West) got 12 points each from J.J. Avila and Joe de Ciman. The Rams shot 40.4 percent from the field for the game (21 of 52) and converted 6 of 21 from long range. San Jose State (2-16, 0-6) converted just 10 of 48 attempts from the field and knocked down 4 of 23 from distance. Rashad Muhammad led the Spartans with 12 points. Isaac Thornton contributed 11 points.
